The '''New Republic army''' was the [[Ground warfare|land-based]] branch of the [[New Republic]]'s [[New Republic Defense Force|Defense Force]] concerned with [[planet]]ary surface tasks and operations. Following the [[Battle of Endor]], New Republic [[army]] personnel took part in battles on numerous [[Planet|worlds]] including [[Naalol]], [[Uyter]], [[Sevarcos]], [[Nag Ubdur]], and [[Jakku]].

==Description==
[[New Republic]] [[army]] [[New Republic soldier|soldiers]] wore simple vest and utility [[belt]]s. They were also equipped with rifles and [[blaster]]s.<ref name="Aftermath" /> Members of the New Republic army came from various different [[species]].<ref name="SWBF">''[[Star Wars Battlefront]]''</ref> Some known units included the [[New Republic Thirty-First]],<ref name="A:LD" /> the [[Third Recon Group]],<ref name="BS:J" /> and the [[61st Mobile Infantry]].<ref name="SF" />

==History==
===Galactic Civil War===
The New Republic army were the ground forces of the [[New Republic Defense Force]], which originated from the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic|Rebel Alliance's]] [[Alliance Army|ground forces]]. Following the [[Battle of Endor]], New Republic [[soldier]]s saw action during the [[Battle of Naalol]], the [[Battle in Central City]], and the [[Battle on Sevarcos]] in [[4 ABY]].<ref name="Aftermath" /> Later, a ground forces unit known as the [[New Republic Thirty-First]] [[Battle of Nag Ubdur|fought]] with [[Galactic Empire|Imperial]] [[Imperial Military|forces]] on [[Nag Ubdur]]<ref name="A:LD" /> in [[5 ABY]].<ref name="A:LD Date">''[[Star Wars: Timelines]]'' dates the events of ''[[Aftermath: Life Debt]]'' to [[5 ABY]].</ref> New Republic soldiers were sometimes accompanied by embedded [[HoloNet]] [[journalist]]s including [[Tracene Kane]] and [[Lug]] from the [[Queen of the Core Network]].<ref name="A:LD" />

The army took part in the [[Battle of Jakku]], a major battle which ended the [[Galactic Civil War]] in the New Republic's favor and led to the signing of the [[Galactic Concordance]]. During the battle, New Republic ground forces on Jakku were commanded by [[Lieutenant General]] [[Brockway]], who corresponded with [[General]] [[Tyben]]. New Republic ground forces were landed by [[UT-60D U-wing starfighter/support craft|U-wings]] and lay siege to the [[main Imperial base]] and other Imperial installations. Despite the signing of the Galactic Concordance, New Republic forces were locked in fighting against the Imperials for several [[Standard month|months]].<ref name="A:EE">''[[Aftermath: Empire's End]]''</ref>

===Rise of the First Order===
After the Battle of [[Endor]], [[Chancellor (New Republic)|Chancellor]] [[Mon Mothma]] made it clear that she wanted to demilitarize and make the remaining military a peacekeeping force.<ref name="Aftermath" /> The New Republic did heavily demilitarize through the [[Military Disarmament Act]].<ref name="SW:TFA:TVD">''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens: The Visual Dictionary]]''</ref>

During the reign of the First Order, New Republic soldiers appeared in several training simulators where the [[First Order]] [[First Order stormtrooper|stormtrooper]] [[Finn|FN-2187]] and his fellow [[cadet]]s assaulted a Republic outpost. While FN-2187 was able to [[Death|kill]] the simulated soldiers, he found himself unable to kill civilians.<ref name="BtA" />

==Organization==
The New Republic soldier composed the army of the New Republic, and saw action in the Battle of Jakku.<ref name="Aftermath" />

==Vehicles and machinery==
Several vehicles were used by the New Republic army, including the [[UT-60D U-wing starfighter/support craft]] and the [[T-47 airspeeder]].<ref name="SWBF" />

==Weapons and equipment==
As the [[Galactic Civil War]] draw to a close, most weapons, vehicle, and equipment were of the rebellion era. But over time, weapons like the [[A280 blaster rifle]] were phased out in favor of newer weapons such as the [[EL-16HFE blaster rifle]].<ref name="SW:TFA:TVD" /> Other weapons used by the army of the New Republic were the [[A280C blaster rifle]], the [[E-11 medium blaster rifle]],<ref name="SWBF2">''[[Star Wars Battlefront II]]''</ref> the [["Roba" M-45 repeating ion blaster]],<ref name="A:EE" /> the [[DH-17 blaster pistol]],<ref name="SWBF" /> and the [[DL-44 heavy blaster pistol]].<ref name="A:LD" /> The army also employed [[thermal detonator]]s, [[thermal imploder]]s, and [[Sonic Imploder]]s.<ref name="SWBF2" />

